%!PS
% ----------------------------------------------------------------------
%                            EXERCISE 5.35
% ----------------------------------------------------------------------
% Modify the Koch star program in Figure 5.13 to produce a different
% fractal based on a five-line figure for order 0, defined by 1-unit
% moves east, north, east, south, and east, in that order (see
% Figure 4.3).
% ----------------------------------------------------------------------
%
% I've simply combined the kochR procedure from figure 5.13 (with minor
% changes) with the solution to E04.13.
%
% According to [Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Koch_snowflake)
% this is called a quadratic Koch curve.

<< /PageSize [125 300] >> setpagedevice
/kochR {
  2 copy gt {dup 0 rlineto}
  {
    3 div
    2 copy kochR
    90 rotate
    2 copy kochR
    -90 rotate
    2 copy kochR
    -90 rotate
    2 copy kochR
    90 rotate
    2 copy kochR
  } ifelse
  pop pop
} def

0.2 setlinewidth
0 0 moveto
125 125 kochR
0 75 moveto
25 125 kochR
0 150 moveto
5 125 kochR
0 225 moveto
1 125 kochR
stroke
